## Standard Operating Procedure (SOP)

Version 1.0

## Effective Date: 5/16/2023

### 1. Purpose:

   The purpose of this SOP is to outline the necessary guidelines required to ensure the use of PSREMOTE and RDP so that users can access a remote computer.

### 2. Responsibilities:

   The IT department shall be responsible for installing PSREMOTE and RDP to company systems, including configuring the settings on the remote computer, 
   ensuring that the necessary security protocols are in place, and setting up the account credentials for the users to access the remote computer. The IT department is also responsible for providing technical support and troubleshooting any issues that arise.

### 3. Procedure:

   A. Install PSREMOTE and RDP

### 1. Run PowerShell as administrator on both client and host machines.


### 2. Run Enable -PSRemoting -Force
   
          
### 3. Run Set-Item wsman:\localhost\client\trustedhosts *

### 4. Enable Windows Remote Management service. This can be done by running the following command in PowerShell: Enable-WSManCredSSP -Role Client –DelegateComputer * -Force.

### 5. Test the connection using Test-WSMan [Ip address]


### FAQ's

Q: Q: How do I enable PSREMOTE and RDP?

A: To enable PSREMOTE and RDP, launch the Remote Desktop Connection app on your computer, enter the IP address or hostname of the computer you wish to access in the Computer field, 
click the Options button, click the Advanced tab, select the “Enable Remote Desktop Protocol” radio button, select the “Allow Remote Desktop Protocol from any version (less secure)” 
radio button, select the “Allow me to save credentials” checkbox, click the OK button, enter your credentials for the remote computer in the Username and Password fields, and click the Connect button.

Q: Q: What are the IT department's responsibilities for installing PSREMOTE and RDP to company systems?

A: The IT department is responsible for ensuring that all systems have the Remote Desktop Connection app installed and configured correctly. The IT department must also ensure that all users have the 
correct credentials to access the remote computer. Additionally, the IT department is responsible for setting up a secure network to allow remote access.
  
